TITLE: Ukrainian city of Severodonetsk now 'completely under Russian occupation' after months of fighting
SUMMARY: The eastern Ukrainian city of Severodonetsk is "completely under Russian occupation," the city's head of military administration said Saturday, following months of grueling and bloody fighting.

SUMMARY: A suspect is at large after a shooting at a WeatherTech facility in Bolingbrook, Ilinois, on Saturday morning, according to the Bolingbrook Police Department.

TITLE: Tear gas used to disperse protesters outside Arizona Capitol building, officials say
SUMMARY: After the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade on Friday, holding that there is no longer a federal constitutional right to an abortion, protesters and supporters of the ruling gathered at the high court's building in Washington, DC, and in other cities nationwide.

SUMMARY: The Supreme Court on Monday made it much more difficult for immigrants to challenge immigration policies in court, holding that challenges have to be brought individually and not on a class-wide basis.

SUMMARY: A suspected land mine was removed from a Florida beach, according to police.

Wade and Republicans previewed new national and state-level efforts to limit abortion rights.
